\f1\b Energy
\f0\b0  Division announced Monday. \
People who make, sell and install 
\f1\b renewable
\f0\b0  
\f1\b energy
\f0\b0  products and services will have products on hand to look at, ask questions about and purchase. On Aug. 1, fair officials scheduled a series of free classes that highlight a range of 
\f1\b renewable
\f0\b0  
\f1\b energy
\f0\b0  topics including hands-on solar system installation, anaerobic digestion, geothermal heat systems, small and large-scale wind power systems and 
\f1\b energy
\f0\b0  efficiency issues. \
The two-day fair, free to the public, will be held in and around the Evergreen Building on the CSI campus. The fair will be open 10 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. Aug. 1, and 10 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Aug. 2. \
Opening ceremonies are set for 9:30 a.m. Aug. 1. \
"The fair is a wonderful chance for folks to see these systems first hand and to ask questions about things like biofuels, solar electric and wind systems. If you've ever wondered if a 
\f1\b renewable
\f0\b0  
\f1\b energy
\f0\b0  system is right for you, this is the time to find out," Gerry Galinato, of the Idaho 
\f1\b Energy
\f0\b0  Division, said in a statement. \
